tartiflette
via Allison Sheehan

tartilflette

10 boiled potatoes small cubes
4 big onions thinly chopped
200g diced bacon or ham
butter 1/3 bottle dry white wine
cream 20cl
rablichon cheese (or any tasty soft white melting cheese)

caramelise the onions with butter

add the bacon, cook for a few minutes

add the wine and cook for a few minutes

add the cream and cook for a more minutes then set aside

Add half the potatoes to a large baking dish, then half the cream mixture, then the rest of the potatoes and then the rest of the cream mixture.

Put the rablichon on top and bake @ 150C until cheese is melted and golden on the top.